Bootstrap: handle nixpkgs sysroot cross-build hazards

Five hunks for nixpkgs cross-rustc to build cleanly:

  lib.rs:
    - cp_link_r: treat symlinks-to-dirs as dirs. Nixpkgs rustc.nix
      symlinks lib/rustlib/<host-triple> across stages; stock logic
      replicates the symlink in /build pointing to /nix/store, so
      subsequent writes fail with EACCES.
    - copy_link_internal: always fs::copy (no hard_link), preempt
      chmod non-symlink ancestors, retry + rich diagnostic on fail.

  compile.rs:
    - LLVM_TOOLS install: skip tools missing at src_path, not just
      when llvm_from_ci. Nixpkgs splits LLVM outputs — llvm-config
      is in -dev/bin and the tools are in out/bin.
    - rust-objcopy copy: guard with src.exists().

